H1> Managing links

P> The Links admin owns both the main navigation menu and the public Links page. Both share the same storage and category model.

Q> How can I enter a link so that it appears in my main navigation menu?
A> Add the link under the [b]Main[/b] category. Anything in that category renders inside the main navigation menu of the active theme. Links in any other category appear on the public Links page.

Q> What's the link button text box for?
A> It defines the button image used to represent the link on the Links page. If you leave it blank a placeholder/empty button is shown instead.

TIP> Use clear, short captions for links in the Main category – the navigation menu has limited horizontal space and long captions wrap or truncate depending on the theme.

NOTE> Visibility rules for links honour user classes (see the Classes help page), so you can publish "members-only" links that guests never see.
